William V. MURRY, Appellant, v. Dr. H. F. DeMESQUITA, Appellee. No. 22276. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. Feb. 9, 1966. Rehearing Denied April 29, 1966. William V. Murry, Hattiesburg, Miss., for appellant. Leonard B. Melvin, Jr., Laurel, Miss., Melvin, Melvin & Melvin, Laurel, Miss., for appellee.

Before GEWIN and COLEMAN, Circuit Judges, and McRAE, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Substantial evidence appearing on the record to support the jury’s verdict, the judgment below is

Affirmed.
